  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , each entry of the cost matrix encodes the cost of a node substitution, deletion or insertion. Substitution costs are defined using the Hungarian algorithms on the set of incident edges of both vertices. The substitution cost of two incident edges takes into account the label of the edge and the label of its incident vertices.",
